  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2015 flood recovery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Individuals,Clergy/Lay Leaders</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of this program is to assist parishes and communities in responding to the needs of the most vulnerable, needs that occurred as a result of the September 2013 flooding in the Front Range, particularly affecting Larimer, Weld and Boulder counties.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">provide direct assistance to families and individuals recovering from the floods of September, 2013, with special attention to the needs of the most vulnerable: the elderly, the poor, and the handicapped. ,Continue to seek those persons in need of assistance not only through regular and ongoing participation in the LTRG process where it exists but also through building and expanding relationships with parishes and Jubilee ministries that serve the vulnerable. ,Use the recovery process as a way of elevating the issue of affordable housing as an arena for action in the Diocese and in communities, particularly focusing on increasing capacity for advocacy on the congregational level,Continue to recruit and provide opportunities for faith-based organizations to participate in the recovery and rebuilding process, with special attention to recruiting and providing volunteer experiences for Episcopal parish-based groups. ,To support, empower and monitor congregations that are currently participating in the 2014 mini-grant programs, parish-based programs designed to assist in recovery and resilience. ,Continued development of a Diocesan Disaster Preparedness Team, Implementing the Year of Resilience as outlined in Appendix A of the Program Planning Worksheet,Continued efforts to expand and utilize the Episcopal Relief and Development asset map, with the goal of having fifteen congregations active on the map by July 1;, Complete diocesan disaster planning and documentation</narrative>
  </description>
